                       "message":  "ai-dispatch ISSUE-210: manual salvage of round-2 EXEC (scrub stale change.md citations)\n\nRound-2 autonomous control exhausted MaxCorrectionRounds with three\nconsecutive needs_changes verdicts on a narrow report-accuracy class:\nthe EXEC report kept quoting stale Phase 9 change.md line citations\nin its correction-history narrative, comparison tables, and\ntool-counting notes — then asserted no stale citations remained,\nwhich was false within the same report.\n\nThis human-directed salvage adds a clean EXEC artifact at\nai_handoffs/ISSUE-210_EXEC_2026-05-26_17-00-00+0300.md (and sidecar)\nthat preserves every substantive finding from the round-2 EXEC while\nremoving every literal stale citation and every correction-history\nphrasing that quoted them. Verdict is unchanged: still coherent.\n\nVerification:\n- rg over salvage EXEC for forbidden stale tokens: 0 matches\n- rg over salvage EXEC for correction-history phrases: 0 matches\n- rg over salvage EXEC for canonical Select-String citations: 12 matches\n- git diff --check: exit 0\n- No tracked-file changes; only the new salvage EXEC + sidecar are added\n\nPrior EXEC reports (round-0/1/2), correction packets, and verification\nlogs are preserved unmodified as historical evidence.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
